# Accessibility audit reference

When the user mentions **accessibility**, **VoiceOver**, **WCAG**, **a11y**, **Dynamic Type**, **hit targets**, or **inclusive design**:

1. **Read first:** [`accessibility/audits/2026-06-13-voiceover-accessibility-audit.md`](../../accessibility/audits/2026-06-13-voiceover-accessibility-audit.md)
2. **Link it** in the reply so the user can open the full report.
3. **Cross-check** open work against [`accessibility/Manual_todo.md`](../../accessibility/Manual_todo.md) and [`accessibility/wcag-2.1-aa/SUMMARY.md`](../../accessibility/wcag-2.1-aa/SUMMARY.md).
4. **New audits:** add a dated file under `accessibility/audits/` and update this rule’s path if superseded.

Do not re-audit from scratch unless the user asks for a fresh pass or the prior audit is stale (major UI changes, fixes landed).
